What is Fahdu?

FAHDU is a creator-user engagement platform where users can interact via chat, audio calls, subscribe and follow creators.

How to sign up on Fahdu?
 Option 1: Continue with Google
Open FAHDU app
Click “Continue with Google”
Select Google account
Grant required permissions
If authentication is successful → User is redirected to the app
Proceed to Agreement Screen (if first-time user)
Option 2: Continue with Apple (iOS Users)
Open FAHDU app
Click “Continue with Apple”
Authenticate using Apple ID (Face ID / Password)
Grant permissions
If authentication is successful → User is redirected to the app
Proceed to Agreement Screen
Option 3: Manual Signup (Email & Password)
Step 1: Registration Form
Click “Sign Up”
Enter:
Valid Email Address
Password-Password must contains - 8 Characters, An Uppercase, A Lower case, A Number & A Special Character
Confirm Password
Click “Sign Up” button
Step 2: Email Verification
After signup, a popup appears:
 “Verify your email”
User checks their registered email inbox
Receives verification email from FAHDU
Clicks “Confirm Email” button in email
User is redirected back to the FAHDU app
Step 3: Agreement & Continue Screen
After verification:
User sees “Agree & Continue” screen
Toggle button to accept Terms & Conditions
Click “Continue” button
Account is successfully created
User is redirected to home

How to login on Fahdu?
Option 1: Continue with Google
Open FAHDU app
Click “Continue with Google”
Select your Google account
Grant required permissions
If authentication is successful → User is logged in
Redirected to Home/Dashboard
Option 2: Continue with Apple (iOS Users)
Open FAHDU app
Click “Continue with Apple”
Authenticate using Apple ID (Face ID / Password)
Grant permissions
If authentication is successful → User is logged in
Redirected to Home/Dashboard
 Option 3: Manual Login (Email & Password)
Click “Login” button
Enter:
Registered Email Address
Password
Click “Login” button
If credentials are correct → Login successful
Redirected to Home
Login Failure Cases
Incorrect email or password → Error message shown
Email not verified → User asked to verify email
Suspended/blocked account → Access denied
How to Recover Your FAHDU Account Password
If you forget your FAHDU account password, you can reset it by following the steps below.
Note: If you originally signed up using Continue with Google or Continue with Apple, you can simply log in again using those methods. Password reset is only required for manual email/password accounts.
Reset Password via Email (Manual Login Users)
Step 1: Go to Login Screen
Open FAHDU app
Click “Login”
Enter your registered email
On the password screen, click “Forgot Password?”


Step 2: Request OTP
Enter your registered email address
Click “Send Code”
An OTP (One-Time Password) is sent to your registered email


Step 3: Verify OTP
Check your email inbox
Copy the OTP
Enter the OTP on the verification screen
Click “Verify”
If OTP is correct → You proceed to the reset password screen.
Step 4: Set New Password
Enter your new password
Confirm your new password
Password Requirements:
Password must contain:
Minimum 8 characters
At least one uppercase letter
At least one lowercase letter
At least one number
At least one special character
Final Step
Password is successfully updated
You can now log in using your new password

FAHDU – Role Selection Flow (After Signup)
 First-Time User Role Selection
After completing the signup process and logging in for the first time, users are shown a role selection module.
The screen asks:
“Are you a Creator?”
 Options: Yes / No
If User Selects “Yes” (Creator)
User clicks “Yes”
User is redirected to the Get Verified page
User must complete the verification process
After verification approval, creator features become accessible
Purpose:
This flow ensures that only verified creators can access creator-specific features.
 If User Selects “No” (Regular User)
User clicks “No”
User is redirected to the Discover Page
User can:


Browse creators
Follow creators
Start chat
Book audio calls
Important Notes
This screen appears only for first-time login.
Role selection determines available features inside the app.

